Portland, Ore. A recent best-selling album and a recent best-selling children's book have two things in common. Their words and drawings were created by the same husband-and-wife team, and they were both inspired by where the couple lives: a steep, windy, densely foliaged neighborhood across from a dark forest of ivy-covered trees filled with coyotes and owls. Photos: A Home in the Urban Wild
